result.execSummary:
The defendant Catrina Delphina Hanz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca(2nd+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Neglecting a Child, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Catrina Delphina Hanz in court.  John E. Flynn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.

Per the probation agent, court ordered case scheduled within 100 days of the defendant's release from prison.
Case scheduled for a probation review hearing on 06/16/2017 at 01:30 pm, Branch 36.
cab

Sentencing proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 2 YEARS and 6 MONTHS, consecutive to Count 3 and any other sentence, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 1 YEAR and 6 MONTHS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 year. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 30 MONTHS. 

AS TO COUNT 3
The court sentenced the defendant to 8 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to Count 1 and any other sentence, straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 MONTHS. If revoked, the defendant may serve sentence in the Wisconsin State Prison System.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION
-Serve 50 DAYS (as to Count 1) in HOC as Condition Time, STAYED pending review.
-Parenting classes.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety.
-No contact with victim HVH unless approved by Children's Court, this Court, or the agent.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
-Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA surcharge to be paid during period of probation, if revoked to be paid from 25% of prison funds, balance paid during Extended Supervision, failure to pay results in a civil judgment. 
-All NON-Mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges due to inability to pay.
-Provide DNA Sample.

*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.

*Probation Review Hearing to be set within 100 days of release. 

Filed: Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Memorandum of Conditions of Probation, Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement, Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence, Judgment of Conviction.
